## M23: extern call from a safe context is still rejected even
## when the extern is declared via the new body-less `extern fun`
## form. The M21 raw-at-call-site enforcement keys off
## `Symbol.kind == .@"extern"`, which both the legacy `extvar`
## form and the new `extern_fun` form set, so the diagnostic
## fires uniformly.

extern fun puts(s: String) -> Int

sub main()
  puts("hi")       # error: extern call requires `raw` block
